org.eclipse.gef4.mvc.fx.tools

Interface ITargetPolicyResolver

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultTargetPolicyResolver

    public interface ITargetPolicyResolver
    The ITargetPolicyResolver provides a mechanism to determine and prioritize all policies that are to be notified about certain input events (see getTargetPolicies(ITool, Node, Class) for details).

    • Method Detail

      • getTargetPolicies

        <T extends IPolicy<javafx.scene.Node>> java.util.List<? extends T> getTargetPolicies(ITool<javafx.scene.Node> contextTool,
                                                                                     javafx.scene.Node target,
                                                                                     java.lang.Class<T> policyClass)
        Determines and prioritizes all policies of the specified type for the given target Node that are to be notified about an input event that was directed at the Node.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type parameter specifying the type of policy that is collected.
        Parameters:
        contextTool - The ITool for which to determine target policies.
        target - The target Node that received an input event.
        policyClass - The type of the policies to return.
        Returns:
        All matching policies within the hierarchy from the root part to the target part.

      • getTargetPolicies

        <T extends IPolicy<javafx.scene.Node>> java.util.List<? extends T> getTargetPolicies(ITool<javafx.scene.Node> contextTool,
                                                                                     javafx.scene.Node target,
                                                                                     IViewer<javafx.scene.Node> viewer,
                                                                                     java.lang.Class<T> policyClass)
        Determines and prioritizes all policies of the specified type for the given IViewer and target Node that are to be notified about an input event that was directed at the Node.
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type parameter specifying the type of policy that is collected.
        Parameters:
        contextTool - The ITool for which to determine target policies.
        target - The target Node that received an input event.
        viewer - The IViewer that contains the given target Node.
        policyClass - The type of the policies to return.
        Returns:
        All matching policies within the hierarchy from the root part to the target part.
